<issue
   id="RBN-1"
   type="mim"
   linkend="Ap239_document_management_mim.ap239_dm_classified_attribute_select"
   status="closed"
   category="editorial"
   by="Rob Bodington"
   date="03-01-07">
<description>
Where an inherited attribute is being classified, the classification is
done at the subtype level as opposed to the supertype in which the
attribute is declared. So the subtype is included in this select.
  <p>
    E.g. 
    The 'name' attribute on the entity 
    <express_ref
      linkend="qualified_measure_schema:ir_express:qualified_measure_schema.descriptive_representation_item"/> 
    is being classified.
    The attribute is inherited from the entity
    <express_ref
      linkend="representation_schema:ir_express:representation_schema.representation_item"/>.    
  </p>
</description>
</issue>


